CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, February 14, 1938, pg. 22, reads: "'Trucking On Down.' Lena Horne of the wining smile cuts some fancy steps at the farewell party given in her honor at the Loendi Club Parlors in Pittsburgh last week. Earl McDonald, D.C. sportsman, and Teddy Horne, Lena's father are looking on."
TitMainTitle: Lena Horne with hands clasped, standing in middle of group of men including father Teddy Horne, and Earl McDonald standing in background in Loendi Club
